<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="content" -->
  <h1>The blue whale </h1>
  <p>
  <img src="images/whale2b.gif" alt="Blue whale" width="420" height="100" border="0" />
  </p>
  <p class="alignleft">
  <span class="bold">The biggest animal ever</span><br />
  The blue whale is probably the biggest animal that has ever lived on Earth. It is hard to imagine how big they are, but have a look at the scale on the picture - that's an adult human being standing next to it! Here are a few quick facts*.</p>
  <ul class="alignleft" style="margin-right:30px;">
  <li>Maximum length as adult - 110 feet - that's about 30 metres </li>
  <li>Maximum length when born - 23 feet - that's about 7 metres</li>
  <li>Adult diet - can eat up to four tonnes of krill a day - that's about 40 million individual krill a day </li>
  <li>Newborn diet - can drink up to 50 gallons of milk a day - that's almost 200 litres of milk a day</li>
  <li>A blue whale's eye is about the size of a tea cup </li>
  <li>The tongue of a blue whale can be the size of a small car </li>
  <li>A blue whale is equal in weight to 30 bull elephants or about 1830 adult humans </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="alignleft">*Courtesy of the <a href="http://www.acs-sfbay.org/">American Cetacean Society</a> and the <a href="http://www.whalecenter.org">Whale Center of New England</a></p>

  <!-- #BeginLibraryItem "../../../library/thezone/furthernavigation/animals/ee-whale.lbi" -->
<p class="yellowbox"><a href="whale.htm#whale" title="Return to the blue whale page">Return to the blue whale page and learn more about the other images</a>.</p>
